      "content": "I can help you craft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a draft:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your exceptional technical skills and the time you took to prepare for our interviews. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and experience better align with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. You demonstrated a high level of expertise and passion for your craft, and we appreciate the effort you put into our process. I'm sure you'll find a great opportunity that's a perfect fit for you.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck in your job search. If you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nI've kept the tone professional and kind, while still conveying that we've decided to go with another candidate. You can adjust the language to fit your company's voice and style.",
